  "pages": [
    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "A meeting of the union depot\ncommittee, recently appointed, will\nbe held at 2 o'clock tomorrow aft\nernoon at which time the presi-\ndents and general managers of the\nroads interested will be on hand to\nexpress their views of the union\ndepot idea.\n\n\nAt this meeting the first definite\ninformation as to the feelings of\nthe railroads will be had, and on\nit's outcome will hinge largely the\nfate of the union depot project.\n\n\nAt the meeting this morning.\nChief Engineer Dittman of the\nNorth Coast submitted plan for\nunion depot to be built along\nFront avenue between Howard and\nWashington street. which would\ninclude the site of the present city\nhall."
    }
  ]
